<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> bet on the wrong horse • put the saddle on the wrong horse</xh5><p> <i>bet on the wrong horse</i>—(also: back the wrong horse) base one’s plans, etc. on a wrong guess about smth.: To count on the family farm as an important thing in the American future looks like <u>betting on the wrong horse</u>.</p><p> <i>put the saddle on the wrong horse</i>—(also: get the wrong pig by the tail) lay the blame on the wrong person: Blaming the teacher for the lazy student’s academic failure is <u>putting the saddle on the wrong horse</u>.</p> </entry>
